
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-dong-idr-rtc-hierarchical-rr-02.txt'>
    <title>"Extensions to RT-Constrain in Hierarchical Route Reflection Scenarios", Jie Dong, Mach Chen, Robert Raszuk</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-dong-idr-rtc-hierarchical-rr-02.txt</link>
    <description>The Route Target (RT) Constrain mechanism specified in RFC 4684 is used to build a route distribution graph in order to restrict the propagation of Virtual Private Network (VPN) routes.  In network scenarios where hierarchical route reflection (RR) is used, the existing RT-Constrain mechanism cannot build a correct route distribution graph.  This document describes the problem scenario and proposes a solution to address the RT-Constrain issue in hierarchical RR scenarios.</description>
    <dc:date>2014-11-25T08:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
